-announces-arrests-in-1989-cold-case%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EArchival%20footage%20shot%20on%20March%205%2C%201989%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20by%20the%20local%20NBC%20affiliate%20WCBD%20showed%20Victor%20Lee%20Turner%20emerging%20from%20a%20camper%20and%20sobbing%20in%20apparent%20grief%20after%20purportedly%20discovering%20his%20son's%20corpse.%20At%20a%20news%20conference%20this%20week%2C%20Berkeley%20County%20Sheriff%20S.%20Duane%20Lewis%20told%20reporters%20authorities%20now%20believe%20the%20Turners%20killed%20the%20child%20inside%20their%20house%2C%20then%20moved%20his%20body%20into%20the%20camper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20look%20at%20the%20scene%2C%20you%20can%20assume%20by%20looking%20at%20it%20that%20it%20was%20somewhat%20a%20staged%20scene%2C%20to%20make%20it%20look%20like%20something%20that%20it%20wasn't%2C%26quot%3B%20Lewis%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20inconsistencies%20in%20the%20story.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELewis%20said%20investigators%20have%20been%20working%20for%20at%20least%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20straight%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20for%20many%20years%20on%20and%20off%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0to%20solve%20the%20cold%20case.%20Lewis%20said%20due%20to%20more%20advanced%20technology%2C%20investigators%20were%20able%20to%20collect%20more%20physical%20evidence%20and%20submit%20it%20to%20forensic%20pathologists%20for%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELewis%20told%20reporters%20that%20initially%2C%20the%20Turners%20told%20authorities%20that%20Justin%20got%20on%20his%20school%20bus%20on%20the%20morning%20of%20March%203%2C%201989%2C%20and%20never%20returned.%20But%20Lewis%20said%20that%20was%20a%20lie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJustin%20never%20made%20it%20to%20school%20that%20morning.%20He%20never%20got%20on%20the%20bus%2C%20he%20never%20arrived%20at%20school.%20That's%20because%20he%20had%20been%20murdered.%20And%20he'd%20been%20murdered%20by%20his%20stepmother%20and%20his%20father%2C%20and%20left%20in%20a%20camper%20behind%20their%20house%2C%26quot%3B%20Lewis%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20think%20of%20a%20more%20tragic%2C%20horrendous%20murder.%20A%20five-year-old%20boy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20attorney%20representing%20Megan%20Renee%20Turner%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment.%20BI%20could%20not%20immediately%20reach%20an%20attorney%20representing%20Victor%20Lee%20Turner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffather-stepmother-charged-1989-cold-case-murder-5-year-old-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705189730000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a3214bdcdb354a9857761b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffather-stepmother-charged-1989-cold-case-murder-5-year-old-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Berkeley%20County%20sheriff%20said%20investigators%20believe%20the%20suspects%20%26quot%3Bstaged%26quot%3B%20a%20scene%20to%20cover%20up%20their%20part%20in%20the%20murder%20of%20a%205-year-old%20boy%20in%201989.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mmark%40businessinsider.com%20(Michelle%20Mark)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffather-stepmother-charged-1989-cold-case-murder-5-year-old-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20quit%20being%20a%20lawyer%20to%20dabble%20in%20writing%20and%20podcasting.%20It%20was%20one%20of%20the%20best%20decisions%20I've%20ever%20made.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221179%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ex-lawyer%20Ling%20Yah%20Wong%20glacier%20hiking%20at%20the%20S%C3%B3lheimaj%C3%B6kull%20Glacier%20in%20Iceland.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a0e3e76979d7371822b6b2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22864%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELing%20Yah%20Wong%2C%2033%2C%20worked%20as%20a%20lawyer%20for%2010%20years%20before%20she%20decided%20to%20quit%20her%20job.%20She's%20now%20a%20personal%20branding%20strategist%2C%20podcaster%2C%20and%20writer.%3Cp%3ELing%20Yah%20Wong%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELing%20Yah%20Wong%20worked%20as%20a%20lawyer%20for%2010%20years%20after%20graduating%20from%20law%20school.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20decided%20to%20quit%20her%20job%20after%20she%20realized%20being%20a%20lawyer%20just%20wasn't%20something%20she%20enjoyed.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWong%20dabbled%20in%20podcasting%20and%20is%20now%20working%20as%20a%20personal%20branding%20strategist.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Flingyah%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELing%20Yah%20Wong%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20who%20left%20the%20legal%20industry%20to%20become%20a%20personal%20branding%20strategist%20and%20podcaster.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20her%20employment%20history.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20know%20what%20I%20wanted%20to%20study%20in%20college.%20My%20GCE%20A%20Level%20subjects%20in%20high%20school%20were%20mathematics%2C%20history%2C%20and%20English%20literature.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20I%20thought%20I%20would%20major%20in%20English%20literature%20because%20the%20subject%20felt%20easy.%20I%20didn't%20really%20have%20to%20study%20for%20it.%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20just%20reading%20stories%20and%20could%20get%20A's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20took%20the%20advice%20of%20my%20school's%20career%20advisors%2C%20who%20said%20that%20people%20with%20my%20subject%20combination%20would%20usually%20study%20law.%20They%20told%20me%20law%20was%20a%20prestigious%20field%20that%20offered%20flexibility%20as%20well.%20You%20could%20pivot%20to%20something%20else%20if%20you%20didn't%20like%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20why%20not%20just%20give%20it%20a%20go%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWorking%20as%20a%20lawyer%20was%20exciting%20at%20first%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20working%20at%20an%20international%20law%20firm%20after%20graduating%20from%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%20with%20my%20law%20degree.%20I%20was%20based%20in%20the%20firm's%20Malaysian%20office%2C%20focusing%20on%20intellectual%20property%20litigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20enjoyed%20the%20work%20that%20I%20got%20to%20do.%20Although%20what%20I%20studied%20in%20school%20had%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20the%20job%2C%20I%20could%20see%20the%20practical%20impacts%20of%20our%20work.%20I%20got%20to%20jump%20on%20client%20calls%20and%20work%20directly%20with%20senior%20colleagues%20and%20law%20firm%20partners.%20I%20was%20given%20a%20lot%20of%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBut%20the%20lifestyle%20wasn't%20something%20I%20wanted%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20discomfort%20with%20the%20job%20grew%20after%20I%20better%20understood%20the%20nature%20of%20legal%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20as%20a%20litigator%2C%20I%20had%20to%20read%20case%20law%20all%20the%20time%2C%20and%20I%20just%20didn't%20enjoy%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20colleague%20who%20would%20spend%20his%20weekends%20reading%20case%20law.%20To%20him%2C%20they%20were%20like%20bedtime%20stories.%20He%20would%20chat%20about%20judges%20he%20had%20never%20met%20as%20though%20they%20were%20his%20best%20friends.%20I%20thought%20to%20myself%20then%2C%20%26quot%3BThat's%20just%20not%20me.%20That%20looks%20like%20passion%20and%20love.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20such%20thing%20as%20vacation%20in%20a%20law%20firm.%20It's%20always%20business.%20It's%20always%20work.%20If%20you%20do%20go%20on%20vacation%2C%20you%20absolutely%20have%20to%20bring%20your%20work%20laptop.%20If%20there%20is%20a%20client%20email%2C%20you%20must%20reply%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%20You'd%20probably%20be%20working%20half%20a%20day%2C%20every%20single%20day%20of%20your%20vacation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESenior%20lawyers%20often%20told%20me%20they%20were%20still%20working%20those%20long%20hours%20because%20they%20genuinely%20enjoyed%20the%20work.%20But%20I%20remembered%20looking%20at%20my%20boss%20and%20thinking%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20you.%20And%20if%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20you%2C%20then%20why%20am%20I%20here%2C%20and%20why%20am%20I%20working%20so%20hard%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20have%20a%20problem%20with%20working%20long%20hours.%20I%20just%20didn't%20see%20myself%20grinding%20so%20hard%20to%20do%20work%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGoing%20in-house%20for%20a%20change%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wasn't%20sure%20if%20my%20resentment%20was%20toward%20practicing%20law%20or%20against%20the%20long%20hours%20I%20had%20to%20pull%20as%20a%20litigator.%20That's%20when%20I%20decided%20to%20work%20as%20an%20in-house%20counsel%20for%20an%20international%20conglomerate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20lucky%20to%20work%20under%20a%20general%20counsel%20who%20gave%20me%20exposure%20opportunities.%20I%20got%20to%20work%20on%20the%20company's%20rebranding%20efforts%20and%20participate%20in%20leadership%20conferences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20doing%20so%20many%20different%20things%20in%20this%20new%20role%2C%20and%20that's%20when%20it%20became%20clear%20to%20me%3A%20The%20law%20wasn't%20something%20I%20enjoyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20struggled%20to%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20this%20because%20I%20didn't%20know%20what%20else%20was%20out%20there%20apart%20from%20the%20law.%20I%20didn't%20have%20an%20answer%20to%20that%20question.%20It%20was%20like%20a%20blank%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20my%20friends%20and%20colleagues%20were%20lawyers.%20There%20didn't%20seem%20to%20be%20an%20alternative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EListening%20to%20podcasts%20changed%20my%20life%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221830%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ling%20Yah%20Wong.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a0ff0843bb77284b9c8a21%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221030%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWong%20started%20her%20podcast%20%26quot%3BSo%20This%20Is%20My%20Why%26quot%3B%20in%20June%202020.%3Cp%3ELing%20Yah%20Wong%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20I%20needed%20to%20put%20myself%20out%20there%20and%20gain%20new%20skills.%20I%20didn't%20know%20exactly%20what%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%2C%20but%20I%20knew%20I%20wanted%20to%20create%20something%20personal%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20when%20I%20discovered%20podcasts.%20I%20remembered%20listening%20to%20a%20podcast%2C%20and%20realizing%20that%20two%20strangers%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20world%20felt%20like%20my%20best%20friends%20after%20that%20episode.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20opened%20my%20mind.%20If%20they%20could%20do%20it%2C%20surely%20I%20could%20do%20so.%20I%20decided%20to%20launch%20my%20podcast%20then.%20I%20figured%20I%20could%20use%20the%20podcast%20to%20talk%20to%20people%2C%20build%20a%20network%2C%20and%20figure%20out%20what%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%20with%20my%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20recording%20in%202020%2C%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20I%20was%20still%20working%20as%20an%20in-house%20counsel%20but%20had%20a%20lot%20more%20time%20since%20I%20got%20to%20work%20from%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoing%20the%20podcast%20was%20essentially%20like%20a%20second%20job.%20I%20would%20jump%20into%20podcasting%20after%20each%20workday%2C%20working%20on%20it%20until%201%20to%202%20a.m.%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETaking%20the%20plunge%20and%20leaving%20law%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222406%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Wong%20(right)%20recording%20a%20podcast%20with%20her%20guest%2C%20Malaysian%20artist%20Red%20Hong%20Yi%20(left).%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a0f5266979d7371822b921%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C