22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftim-cook-daily-routine-schedule-apple-ceo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efitness%20buff%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECook%20left%20IBM%20and%20jumped%20into%20a%20COO%20role%20at%20a%20company%20called%20Intelligent%20Electronics.%20He%20eventually%20became%20vice%20president%20of%20corporate%20materials%20at%20Compaq%2C%20then%20one%20of%20the%20hottest%20PC%20manufacturers%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Steve%20Jobs%20had%20just%20come%20into%20power%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-ceo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApple's%20CEO%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20following%20the%20ouster%20of%20Gil%20Amelio.%20Jobs%20had%20the%20tough%20task%20of%20turning%20the%20company%20around%20after%20many%20years%20of%20fading%20relevance.%20He%20went%20looking%20for%20fresh%20blood%20for%20his%20executive%20team.%20Jobs%20approached%20Cook%2C%20identifying%20him%20as%20a%20strong%20prospect%20for%20the%20new%20Apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETim%20Cook%20goes%20to%20Apple%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECook%20signed%20on%20to%20Apple%20in%201998%20as%20SVP%20of%20worldwide%20operations.%20It%20must%20have%20been%20a%20difficult%20decision%20for%20Cook.%20In%201997%2C%20Apple%20was%20an%20industry%20laughingstock%3A%20Michael%20Dell%2C%20one%20of%20Microsoft's%20closest%20partners%2C%20once%20said%20that%20if%20he%20were%20in%20Jobs'%20shoes%2C%20%26quot%3BI'd%20shut%20it%20down%20and%20give%20the%20money%20back%20to%20the%20shareholders.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20experiencing%20Jobs'%20biggest%20flop%20first-hand%20just%20a%20few%20years%20later%20probably%20didn't%20make%20the%20transition%20easier%2C%20either%3A%20In%202000%2C%20Apple%20released%20the%20Power%20Mac%20G4%20Cube%2C%20but%20the%20small%20PC%2C%20which%20Cook%20called%20an%20%26quot%3Bengineering%20marvel%2C%26quot%3B%20never%20found%20its%20audience.%20But%20Cook%20said%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-ceo-tim-cook-on-steve-jobs-and-power-mac-g4-cube-2017-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espectacular%20failure%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20taught%20him%20an%20important%20lesson%20in%20humility%20and%20intellectual%20honesty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20was%20another%20thing%20that%20Steve%20taught%20me%2C%20actually%2C%26quot%3B%20Cook%20said%20during%20a%20visit%20to%20Oxford%20University%20in%202017.%20%26quot%3BYou've%20got%20to%20be%20willing%20to%20look%20yourself%20in%20the%20mirror%20and%20say%2C%20'I%20was%20wrong%2C%20it's%20not%20right.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Cook's%20biggest%20early%20coups%20was%20closing%20Apple's%20own%20factories%20and%20warehouses%20and%20replacing%20them%20with%20contract%20manufacturers%2C%20meaning%20that%20devices%20could%20be%20made%20in%20larger%20quantities%20and%20get%20delivered%20faster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0In%202005%2C%20Cook%20also%20started%20making%20investments%20that%20would%20lay%20the%20groundwork%20for%20the%20future%20of%20the%20company%2C%20including%20forming%20critical%20deals%20with%20manufacturers%20on%20flash%20memory%2C%20the%20computer-storage%20component%20that%20would%20form%20the%20basis%20for%20the%20iPhone%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-apple-ipads%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EiPad%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Cook's%20prescience%20meant%20that%20when%20competitors%20sought%20to%20build%20their%20own%20phones%20and%20tablets%2C%20they%20had%20to%20compete%20for%20what%20little%20factory%20capacity%20and%20components%20those%20factories%20could%20spare%2C%20after%20they%20had%20already%20fulfilled%20their%20commitments%20to%20Apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20Cook's%20management%20expertise%2C%20his%20star%20within%20the%20company%20rose%20rapidly.%20Apple%20was%20on%20the%20track%20toward%20growth%20and%20big%20profits%2C%20and%20Cook%20got%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20credit.%20As%20his%20influence%20grew%2C%20Cook%20became%20known%20within%20the%20company%20for%20his%20no-mercy%2C%20relentless%20questioning%20style%2C%20his%20willingness%20to%20hold%20hours-long%20meetings%2C%20and%20his%20propensity%20for%20sending%20emails%20at%20all%20hours%20and%20expecting%20answers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222052%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Former%20Apple%20CEO%20Steve%20Jobs%20shows%20off%20the%20first%20iPhone%20on%20stage%20at%20an%20Apple%20event%20with%20the%20Apple%20logo%20looming%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659d8986dcdb354a9855f8dc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221588%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20same%20year%20that%20Apple%20debuted%20the%20iPhone%2C%20then-CEO%20Steve%20Jobs%20brought%20Tim%20Cook%20closer%20to%20the%20business'%20core%20as%20COO.%3Cp%3EPaul%20Sakuma%2F%20AP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202007%2C%20Apple%20introduced%20the%20iPhone%20%E2%80%94%20the%20device%20that%20would%20change%20everything.%20That%20same%20year%2C%20Jobs%20brought%20Cook%20closer%20to%20the%20core%20of%20the%20business%20by%20naming%20him%20COO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20COO%2C%20Cook%20helped%20run%20Apple's%20business%20and%20made%20more%20appearances%20at%20public%20events%2C%20getting%20out%20in%20front%20of%20executives%2C%20customers%2C%20partners%2C%20and%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECook%20becomes%20CEO%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202009%2C%20Tim%20Cook%20was%20named%20interim%20CEO%20while%20Steve%20Jobs%20was%20on%20leave%20to%20manage%20his%20declining%20health.%20Jobs%20had%20been%20diagnosed%20with%20pancreatic%20cancer%20in%202003%2C%20and%20it%20was%20starting%20to%20take%20its%20toll.%20Cook%20even%20offered%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-ceo-tim-cook-offered-his-liver-to-steve-jobs-2015-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJobs%20a%20portion%20of%20his%20liver%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20since%20they%20share%20a%20rare%20blood%20type.%20But%20Jobs%20refused%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BI'll%20never%20let%20you%20do%20that.%20I'll%20never%20do%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%202011%2C%20Cook%20took%20over%20as%20interim%20CEO%20once%20again%20while%20Jobs%20was%20on%20medical%20leave.%20In%20August%202011%2C%20Jobs%20resigned%20his%20role%20to%20focus%20on%20his%20health%20%E2%80%94%20the%20board%20then%20named%20Cook%20the%20permanent%20CEO%20of%20Apple.%20When%20Jobs%20died%20in%20October%202011%2C%20Cook%20had%20the%20flags%20on%20the%20campus%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-headquarters-hq%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApple%20headquarters%3C%2Fa%3E%20flown%20at%20half-staff%20in%20his%20memory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECook%20reportedly%20considers%20the%20time%20following%20Jobs'%20death%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftim-cook-advice-on-difference-between-preparation-readiness-steve-jobs-2019-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eloneliest%20time%20of%20his%20life%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Cook%20told%20Stanford%20University's%20graduating%20class%20of%202019%20that%20mentors%20can%20leave%20you%20prepared%20but%20not%20ready.%20Cook%20said%20that%20after%20Jobs'%20death%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhen%20the%20dust%20settled%2C%20all%20he%20knew%20was%20that%20he%20was%20going%20to%20have%20to%20be%20the%20best%20version%20of%20himself%20that%20he%20could%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222999%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tim%20Cook%20stands%20in%20front%20of%20a%20large%20screen%20showing%20a%20chart%20about%20Mobile%20Phone%20Satisfaction.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5d72d9b52e22af2291573382%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222249%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETim%20Cook's%20first%20presentation%20as%20Apple%20CEO%3Cp%3EKevork%20Djansezian%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECook%20had%20some%20big%20shoes%20to%20fill.%20The%20iPhone%2C%20espe