ok_revised.pdf%5C%22%3EState%20of%20Working%20India%20Report%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0focus%20on%20the%20implications%20of%20this%20fact%20on%20women%E2%80%99s%20earnings%20and%20the%20gender-based%20earnings%20gap%20using%20evidence%20from%20official%20employment%20surveys.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEarnings%20gap%20across%20employment%20types%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20compositional%20shift%20away%20from%20casual%20wage%20work%20toward%20regular%20wage%20employment%20narrows%20the%20gender%20earnings%20gap%20because%20the%20gap%20tends%20to%20be%20larger%20in%20the%20former.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202021-22%2C%20the%20average%20monthly%20earnings%20of%20a%20regular%20salaried%20man%20was%20approximately%20Rs.%2017%2C910.%20A%20salaried%20woman%20earned%20about%20Rs.%2013%2C666.%20In%20casual%20wage%20work%2C%20the%20earnings%20disparity%20was%20higher%2C%20with%20women%20earning%20only%2060%25%20of%20what%20men%20earn.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20the%20share%20of%20women%20in%20self-employment%20has%20remained%20stagnant%20over%20most%20of%20the%20post-reform%20period%20(and%20has%20even%20increased%20during%20the%20Covid%20and%20post-Covid%20period).%20This%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20concern%20because%20the%20earnings%20gap%20is%20highest%20in%20the%20case%20of%20self-employment%2C%20with%20women%2C%20on%20average%2C%20earning%20only%2040%25%20of%20men%E2%80%99s%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190006%2FRatios.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22609%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190006%2FRatios.png%20609w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190006%2FRatios-300x138.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692848%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22280%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ETable%3A%20CASI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20do%20these%20disparities%20play%20out%20across%20the%20earnings%20distribution%3F%20As%20women%20move%20up%20the%20earnings%20ladder%2C%20are%20they%20earning%20closer%20to%20what%20men%20make%20or%20does%20the%20gap%20widen%20even%20further%3F%20Figure%201%20(below)%20gives%20us%20an%20answer%20to%20this%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20each%20type%20of%20employment%2C%20we%20divide%20the%20earnings%20into%20ten%20groups%20representing%20the%20lowest%20(decile%201)%20and%20highest%20earners%20(decile%2010).%20As%20we%20see%20in%20Table%201%2C%20across%20the%20earnings%20distribution%2C%20self-employment%20has%20the%20highest%20gender-based%20earnings%20gap.%20By%20contrast%2C%20salaried%20employment%20has%20a%20much%20lower%20earnings%20gap%20and%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20this%20gap%20steadily%20narrows%20as%20one%20moves%20up%20the%20earnings%20distribution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20top%20of%20the%20salaried%20earnings%20spectrum%2C%20women%20earn%2090%25%20of%20what%20men%20earn%2C%20on%20average.%20For%20self-employment%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20earnings%20gap%20is%20still%20high%2C%20with%20women%20earning%20around%2060%25%20of%20what%20men%20make.%20Although%20the%20gender%20earnings%20gap%20in%20self-employment%20narrows%20as%20one%20moves%20up%20the%20earnings%20distribution%2C%20it%20remains%20quite%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190515%2FRatios-by-decile.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22808%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190515%2FRatios-by-decile.png%20808w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190515%2FRatios-by-decile-300x214.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692850%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22577%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EChart%3A%20CASI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrends%20in%20earnings%20gap%20over%20time%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficial%20estimates%20of%20earnings%20from%20self-employment%20have%20only%20been%20collected%20since%202017%2C%20whereas%20we%20have%20information%20on%20wage%20earnings%20from%20the%201980s%20onwards.%20Figure%202%20shows%20the%20long%20run%20trends%20in%20earnings%20gap%20for%20salaried%20workers%20within%20each%20quartile%20group%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190830%2FRatios-per-quartile-and-time.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22835%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190830%2FRatios-per-quartile-and-time.png%20835w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13190830%2FRatios-per-quartile-and-time-300x210.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692851%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22585%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EChart%3A%20CASI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EExplaining%20the%20trends%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClearly%2C%20over%20time%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20narrowing%20of%20the%20earnings%20gap%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20second%20and%20third%20quartiles.%20Two%20possibilities%20can%20explain%20this%20narrowing%20trend.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%2C%20gender-based%20discrimination%20in%20the%20labour%20market%20may%20have%20decreased%20over%20time%2C%20with%20employers%20treating%20men%20and%20women%20similarly.%20Or%20it%20could%20be%20that%20the%20very%20nature%20of%20women%20participating%20in%20the%20labour%20market%20(vis-a-vis%20men)%20has%20changed%2C%20with%20more%20educational%20attainment%20among%20women%20as%20well%20as%20an%20improvement%20in%20the%20kinds%20of%20occupations%20and%20industries%20they%20had%20access%20to%20within%20regular%20salaried%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20mentioned%20earlier%2C%20over%20this%20period%2C%20a%20large%20change%20has%20occurred%20in%20the%20composition%20of%20the%20female%20workforce.%20Older%2C%20less%20educated%20women%20have%20exited%20while%20younger%2C%20more%20educated%20women%20have%20entered.%20Fewer%20women%20are%20employed%20in%20agriculture%20and%20more%20and%20more%20women%20are%20in%20the%20services%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fpandemic-exacerbated-identity-based-discrimination-india-labour-market%5C%22%3EHow%20the%20Pandemic%20Exacerbated%20Identity-Based%20Discrimination%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20Labour%20Market%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20discern%20how%20much%20these%20compositional%20changes%20explain%20the%20changes%20in%20the%20earnings%20gap%20over%20time%2C%20we%20use%20a%20standard%20decomposition%20technique.%20The%20Kitagawa-Oaxaca-Blinder%20decomposition%20considers%20the%20average%20earnings%20difference%20between%20men%20and%20women%20and%20identifies%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20this%20difference%20can%20be%20attributed%20to%20%E2%80%9Cexplained%20differences%E2%80%9D%2C%20i.e.%2C%20differences%20in%20observable%20characteristics%20between%20the%20two%20groups%2C%20and%20to%20%E2%80%9Cunexplained%20differences%E2%80%9D%2C%20i.e.%2C%20differences%20in%20unobservable%20characteristics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EObservable%20characteristics%20include%20education%2C%20marital%20status%2C%20number%20of%20children%2C%20industry%2C%20and%20occupation%20of%20employment.%20The%20unobservable%20component%20is%20often%20interpreted%20as%20measuring%20discrimination%2C%20but%20it%20can%20also%20include%20the%20effect%20of%20omitted%20characteristics%20for%20which%20data%20is%20not%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETable%202%20shows%20the%20extent%20of%20the%20explained%20and%20unexplained%20components%20over%20time.%20From%201983%20onward%2C%20there%20is%20a%20steady%20decline%20in%20the%20explained%20component.%20This%20reflects%20how%20the%20characteristics%20of%20men%20and%20women%20in%20the%20labour%20market%20have%2C%20over%20time%2C%20become%20similar%20and%2C%20hence%2C%20explain%20less%20and%20less%20of%20the%20gender%20wage%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%202021-22%2C%20about%2080%25%20of%20the%20earnings%20gap%20is%20attributable%20to%20this%20unexplained%20component.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13191854%2FOaxaca.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22876%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13191854%2FOaxaca.png%20876w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13191854%2FOaxaca-300x143.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692853%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22417%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ETable%3A%20CASI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20increase%20is%20more%20dramatic%20in%20the%20case%20of%20the%20rural%20workforce%2C%20where%20more%20than%2090%25%20of%20the%20gender%20wage%20gap%20in%202021-22%20was%20not%20explained%20by%20workers%E2%80%99%20characteristics.%20But%20the%20period%20that%20saw%20a%20rapid%20rise%20in%20the%20female%20salaried%20workforce%20(1999%20to%202017)%20did%20also%20see%20a%20rise%20in%20the%20unexplained%20component%20in%20urban%20India%20as%20well.%20Thus%2C%20the%20finding%20is%20a%20general%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20size%20of%20the%20gap%20itself%20increased%20substantially%20in%20rural%20India%20but%20the%20increase%20is%20much%20less%20pronounced%20in%20urban%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20larger%20conclusion%20is%20worth%20emphasising.%20The%20same%20period%20that%20saw%20a%20rapid%20rise%20in%20regular%20wage%20work%20among%20women%20also%20saw%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20unexplained%20part%20of%20the%20gender%20wage%20gap%2C%20usually%20attributed%20to%20discrimination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20two%20decades%20have%20seen%20a%20large%20churn%20in%20the%20Indian%20female%20workforce.%20The%20increase%20in%20the%20share%20of%20women%20as%20salaried%20workers%20is%20good%20news.%20However%2C%20this%20increase%20has%20not%20led%20to%20a%20systematic%20reduction%20in%20the%20unexplained%20earnings%20gap.%20Rather%2C%20educational%20convergence%20has%20revealed%20the%20potential%20role%20of%20discrimination%20in%20causing%20the%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20an%20increase%20in%20education%20and%20improved%20access%20to%20non-agricultural%20employment%2C%20women%20continue%20to%20earn%20less%20than%20men.%20But%20once%20again%2C%20it%20is%20encouraging%20that%2C%20as%20one%20moves%20up%20the%20earnings%20ladder%2C%20the%20gap%20reduces%2C%20which%20may%20reflect%20less%20discriminatory%20conditions%20for%20women%20in%20relatively%20more%20formal%20parts%20of%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20policy%20responses%20that%20encourage%20improved%20access%20to%20education%20for%20girls%20and%20enable%20the%20expansion%20of%20formal%20employment%20can%20help%20narrow%20the%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAmit%20Basole%20and%20Rosa%20Abraham%20are%20faculty%20at%20Azim%20Premji%20University.%20The%20analysis%20presented%20here%20was%20assisted%20by%20Hami%20Ameen%2C%20Research%20Associate%20at%20Azim%20Premji%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20originally%20appeared%20in%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fcasi.sas.upenn.edu%2Fiit%5C%22%3EIndia%20in%20Transition%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20a%20publication%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%E2%80%99s%20Center%20for%20the%20Advanced%20Study%20of%20India.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705156416000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F13200128%2FWorkplace.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fdiscrimination-gender-wage-gap-casi-sas%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20same%20period%20that%20saw%20a%20rapid%20rise%20in%20regular%20wage%20work%20among%20women%20also%20saw%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98unexplained%E2%80%99%20part%20of%20the%20gender%20wage%20gap%2C%20which%20is%20usually%20attributed%20to%20discrimination.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fdiscrimination-gender-wage-gap-casi-sas%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Queen%20Elizabeth%20%26quot%3BDied%20Peacefully%20In%20Her%20Sleep%26quot%3B%2C%20Reveals%20Book%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20memo%20allegedly%20written%20by%20her%20private%20secretary%2C%20Sir%20Edward%20Young%2C%20Queen%20Elizabeth%20II's%20final%20moments%20at%20Balmoral%20were%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bvery%20peaceful%2C%26quot%3B%20without%20pain.%20The%20document%20states%20that%20she%20%26quot%3Bslipped%20away%26quot%3B%20in%20her%20sleep%20when%20she%20died%20and%20%26quot%3Bwouldn't%20have%20been%20aware%20of%20anything%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20information%20is%20disclosed%20in%20a%20new%20biography%20about%20the%20King%2C%20authored%20by%20Robert%20Hardman%2C%20the%20royal%20writer%20for%20the%20Daily%20Mail.%20Buckingham%20Palace%20has%20chosen%20not%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20%26quot%3Bunauthorized%26quot%3B%20biography%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fuk-67967380%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBBC%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3Ereported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20book%2C%20serialized%20in%20the%20Daily%20Mail%2C%20it%20is%20mentioned%20that%20the%20King%20was%20picking%20mushrooms%20nearby%20when%20his%20mother%20died.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20full%20text%20of%20Sir%20Edward's%20memo%20about%20the%20Queen's%20death%20on%20September%208%2C%202022%20reads%2C%20%26quot%3BVery%20peaceful.%20In%20her%20sleep.%20Slipped%20away.%20Old%20age.%20She%20wouldn't%20have%20been%20aware%20of%20anything.%20No%20pain.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20document%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20located%20in%20the%20Royal%20Archives%20and%20constitutes%20a%20segment%20of%20Mr%20Hardman's%20recently%20published%20book%20titled%20%26quot%3BCharles%20III%3A%20New%20King%2C%20New%20Court.%20The%20Inside%20Story.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20biography%2C%20it%20asserts%20that%20a%20securely%20locked%20red%20box%20containing%20two%20sealed%20letters%20was%20discovered%20at%20the%20bedside%20of%20the%20late%20Queen.%20One%20of%20the%20letters%20was%20addressed%20to%20then-Prince%20Charles%2C%20and%20the%20other%20was%20intended%20for%20Sir%20Edward.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20her%20death%2C%20the%20King%20and%20Queen%20Camilla%20spent%20a%20private%20hour%20with%20her%2C%20while%20Princess%20Anne%2C%20a%20minister%20from%20a%20nearby%20church%2C%20and%20the%20late%20Queen's%20senior%20dresser%20took%20turns%20at%20her%20bedside%2C%20as%20per%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERegarding%20the%20King's%20actions%20in%20those%20final%20hours%2C%20the%20Daily%20Mail%20reports%20that%20he%20contacted%20both%20of%20his%20sons%2C%20urging%20them%20to%20promptly%20travel%20to%20Scotland%20to%20bid%20their%20farewells.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Daily%20Mail%2C%20the%20King%2C%20who%20had%20stepped%20out%20to%20collect%20mushrooms%20and%20clear%20his%20thoughts%20after%20visiting%20his%20mother%2C%20learned%20of%20her%20death%20while%20driving%20back%20to%20Balmoral.%20He%20pulled%20over%2C%20and%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20he%20was%20addressed%20as%20%26quot%3BYour%20Majesty%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20described%20in%20the%20biography.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705156140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-09%2Fqltf8beo_queen-elizabeth-ii-_625x300_09_September_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fqueen-elizabeth-died-peacefully-in-her-sleep-book-reveals-4856600%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20memo%20reads%2C%20%26quot%3BVery%20peaceful.%20In%20her%20sleep.%20Slipped%20away.%20Old%20age.%20She%20wouldn't%20have%20been%20aware%20of%20anything.%20No%20pain.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fqueen-elizabeth-died-peacefully-in-her-sleep-book-reveals-4856600%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fqueen-elizabeth-died-peacefully-in-her-sleep-book-reveals-4856600%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fqueen-elizabeth-died-peacefully-in-her-sleep-book-reveals-4856600%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BAmid%20Border%20Issue%2C%20China%20Shouldn't%20Expect...%26quot%3B%3A%20S%20Jaishankar%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAmid%20a%20stand-off%20at%20the%20border%2C%20China%20should%20not%20expect%20other%20relations%20to%20move%20on%20normally%2C%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20S%20Jaishankar%20said%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDiplomacy%20continues%20and%20sometimes%20solutions%20to%20difficult%20situations%20do%20not%20come%20in%20haste%2C%20he%20said%20while%20speaking%20on%20'Bharat's%20Rise%20in%20Geopolitics'%20at%20an%20event%20in%20Nagpur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20borders%20between%20India%20and%20China%20are%20not%20mutually%20agreed%20and%20it%20was%20decided%20that%20both%20sides%20would%20not%20amass%20troops%20and%20would%20keep%20the%20other%20informed%20about%20their%20movements%2C%20he%20said.%20But%20the%20neighbouring%20nation%20violated%20this%20agreement%20in%202020%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20brought%20its%20troops%20in%20large%20numbers%20to%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20(LAC)%20and%20the%20Galwan%20incident%20happened%2C%20S%20Jaishankar%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Minister%20said%20he%20explained%20to%20his%20Chinese%20counterpart%20that%20%26quot%3Bunless%20a%20solution%20is%20found%20at%20the%20border%2C%20they%20should%20not%20expect%20other%20relations%20to%20move%20on%20normally%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20is%20impossible.%20You%20don't%20want%20to%20fight%20and%20do%20trade%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20Meanwhile%2C%20diplomacy%20is%20going%20on%20and%20sometimes%20solutions%20to%20difficult%20situations%20do%20not%20come%20in%20haste%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20asserted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20the%20recent%20rift%20with%20the%20Maldives%2C%20S%20Jaishankar%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20are%20trying%20to%20do%2C%20and%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20success%20in%20the%20last%2010%20years%2C%20is%20to%20build%20a%20very%20strong%20connection.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPolitics%20may%20go%20up%20and%20down%20but%20the%20people%20of%20that%20nation%20generally%20have%20good%20feelings%20towards%20India%20and%20understand%20the%20importance%20of%20having%20good%20relations%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20India%20was%20involved%20in%20building%20roads%2C%20power%20transmission%20lines%2C%20fuel%20supply%2C%20providing%20trade%20access%2C%20investing%20and%20having%20people%20spend%20holidays%20in%20other%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20parts%20of%20how%20a%20relationship%20is%20developed%2C%20though%20sometimes%20things%20do%20not%20go%20the%20right%20way%20and%20one%20has%20to%20reason%20with%20people%20to%20bring%20it%20back%20to%20where%20it%20should%20be%2C%20the%20Minister%20pointed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20the%20United%20Nations%20not%20being%20able%20to%20prevent%20most%20wars%20but%20some%20of%20its%20members%20have%20been%20successful%20in%20denying%20India%20a%20permanent%20seat%20in%20the%20Security%20Council%2C%20S%20Jaishankar%20said%20the%20UN%20used%20to%20be%20relevant%20in%20the%201950s%20and%201960s%20and%20the%20five%20nations%20in%20the%20Security%20Council%20used%20to%20dominate%20other%20countries%20due%20to%20a%20wide%20gap%20between%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20what%20has%20happened%20in%20the%20past%2030-40%20years%2C%20it%20is%20no%20longer%20the%20case%2C%20S%20Jaishankar%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20limitations%20of%20the%20UN%20are%20now%20visible%20and%20many%20people%20believe%20India%2C%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20economies%20in%20the%20world%2C%20must%20be%20there%20(in%20the%20Security%20Council%20as%20a%20permanent%20member).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20pointed%20out%20that%20no%20one%20expected%20a%20united%20outcome%20after%20the%20G20%20meetings%20last%20year%20under%20India's%20presidency%20but%20%26quot%3Bwe%20managed%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20passing%20year%2C%20the%20world%20feels%20India%20should%20be%20there%20but%20the%20world%20does%20not%20give%20things%20easily%20and%20generously.%20%3Cem%3EKabhi%20kabhi%20lena%20padhta%20hai%3C%2Fem%3E%20(sometimes%20we%20need%20to%20step%20forward%20and%20take%20it).%20We%20will%20keep%20moving%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20the%20large%20number%20of%20Indians%20surrendering%20their%20passports%20to%20settle%20abroad%20despite%20India%20being%20the%20fifth%20largest%20economy%20in%20the%20world%2C%20S%20Jaishankar%20said%20it%20was%20a%20personal%20choice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20a%20democracy%2C%20you%20have%20to%20accept%20some%20individual%20choices%20because%20that%20is%20the%20nature%20of%20life.%20But%20the%20best%20answer%20is%20how%20we%20can%20provide%20more%20and%20better%20employment%20opportunities%20in%20India%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Minister%20added%20that%20one%20should%20not%20look%20at%20people%20moving%20abroad%20in%20a%20negative%20way%20since%20it%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20pride%20that%20in%20hospitality%2C%20aviation%2C%20shipping%2C%20etc.%20Indians%20are%20willing%20to%20take%20employment%20to%20contribute.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20wherever%20they%20work%2C%20it%20is%20a%20plus%20point%20for%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20claimed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20some%20of%20the%20prominent%20achievements%20of%20the%20country%20in%20foreign%20affairs%2C%20he%20said%20the%20relationship%20with%20the%20US%20was%20negative%20or%20difficult%20from%201947%20for%20the%20next%2050%20years.%20But%20that%20began%20changing%20for%20the%20better%20under%20the%20prime%20ministership%20of%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee.%20There%20is%20a%20difference%20in%20how%20the%20US%20views%20India%20today%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20recognise%20the%20importance%20India%20holds%2C%20especially%20in%20technology.%20The%20enthusiasm%20in%20American%20businesses%20for%20India%20has%20changed.%20They%20were%20never%20very%20strong%20earlier.%20The%20relationship%20with%20Australia%20has%20changed%20significantly%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20relationship%20with%20Gulf%20nations%20has%20also%20changed%20if%20one%20sees%20the%20trade%2C%20political%2C%20and%20security%20confidence%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNext%20month%20we%20will%20be%20seeing%20the%20opening%20of%20the%20Swaminarayan%20Temple%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi%20(in%20the%20UAE).%20To%20me%20there%20is%20a%20profound%20change%20in%20the%20way%20that%20country%20is%20looking%20at%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E