%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENowadays%20the%20idea%20of%20computers%20storing%20information%20is%20so%20commonplace%20that%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20even%20think%20about%20what%20words%20like%20%E2%80%9Cmemory%E2%80%9D%20really%20mean.%20Back%20in%20the%201950s%2C%20however%2C%20this%20language%20was%20new%20to%20most%20people%2C%20and%20the%20idea%20of%20an%20%E2%80%9Celectronic%20brain%E2%80%9D%20was%20heavy%20with%20possibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20your%20microwave%20has%20more%20computing%20power%20than%20anything%20that%20was%20called%20a%20brain%20in%20the%201950s%2C%20but%20the%20world%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%20is%20posing%20fresh%20challenges%20for%20language%20%E2%80%93%20and%20lawyers.%20Last%20month%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20newspaper%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F12%2F27%2Fbusiness%2Fmedia%2Fnew-york-times-open-ai-microsoft-lawsuit.html%5C%22%3Efiled%20a%20lawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20OpenAI%20and%20Microsoft%2C%20the%20owners%20of%20popular%20AI-based%20text-generation%20tool%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fchat.openai.com%2Fauth%2Flogin%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20over%20their%20alleged%20use%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3ETimes%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20articles%20in%20the%20data%20they%20use%20to%20train%20(improve)%20and%20test%20their%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20claim%20that%20OpenAI%20has%20infringed%20copyright%20by%20using%20their%20journalism%20as%20part%20of%20the%20process%20of%20creating%20ChatGPT.%20In%20doing%20so%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20claims%2C%20they%20have%20created%20a%20competing%20product%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnytco-assets.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F12%2FNYT_Complaint_Dec2023.pdf%5C%22%3Ethat%20threatens%20their%20business%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Fblog%2Fopenai-and-journalism%5C%22%3EOpenAI%E2%80%99s%20response%3C%2Fa%3E%20so%20far%20has%20been%20very%20cautious%2C%20but%20a%20key%20tenet%20outlined%20in%20a%20statement%20released%20by%20the%20company%20is%20that%20their%20use%20of%20online%20data%20falls%20under%20the%20principle%20known%20as%20%E2%80%9Cfair%20use%E2%80%9D.%20This%20is%20because%2C%20OpenAI%20argues%2C%20they%20transform%20the%20work%20into%20something%20new%20in%20the%20process%20%E2%80%93%20the%20text%20generated%20by%20ChatGPT.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20crux%20of%20this%20issue%20is%20the%20question%20of%20data%20use.%20What%20data%20do%20companies%20like%20OpenAI%20have%20a%20right%20to%20use%2C%20and%20what%20do%20concepts%20like%20%E2%80%9Ctransform%E2%80%9D%20really%20mean%20in%20these%20contexts%3F%20Questions%20like%20this%2C%20surrounding%20the%20data%20we%20train%20AI%20systems%2C%20or%20models%2C%20like%20ChatGPT%20on%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fchatgpt-what-the-law-says-about-who-owns-the-copyright-of-ai-generated-content-200597%5C%22%3Eremain%20a%20fierce%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fgenerative-ai-is-a-minefield-for-copyright-law-207473%5C%22%3Eacademic%20battleground%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20law%20often%20lags%20behind%20the%20behaviour%20of%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%E2%80%99ve%20used%20AI%20to%20answer%20emails%20or%20summarise%20work%20for%20you%2C%20you%20might%20see%20ChatGPT%20as%20an%20end%20justifying%20the%20means.%20However%2C%20it%20perhaps%20should%20worry%20us%20if%20the%20only%20way%20to%20achieve%20that%20is%20by%20exempting%20specific%20corporate%20entities%20from%20laws%20that%20apply%20to%20everyone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20could%20that%20change%20the%20nature%20of%20debate%20around%20copyright%20lawsuits%20like%20this%20one%2C%20but%20it%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20change%20the%20way%20societies%20structure%20their%20legal%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFundamental%20questions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECases%20like%20this%20can%20throw%20up%20thorny%20questions%20about%20the%20future%20of%20legal%20systems%2C%20but%20they%20can%20also%20question%20the%20future%20of%20AI%20models%20themselves.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20believes%20that%20ChatGPT%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnytco-assets.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F12%2FNYT_Complaint_Dec2023.pdf%5C%22%3Ethreatens%20the%20long-term%20existence%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20newspaper.%20On%20this%20point%2C%20OpenAI%20says%20in%20its%20statement%20that%20it%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Fblog%2Fopenai-and-journalism%5C%22%3Ecollaborating%20with%20news%20organisations%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20provide%20novel%20opportunities%20in%20journalism.%20It%20says%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20goals%20are%20to%20%E2%80%9Csupport%20a%20healthy%20news%20ecosystem%E2%80%9D%20and%20to%20%E2%80%9Cbe%20a%20good%20partner%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20we%20believe%20that%20AI%20systems%20are%20a%20necessary%20part%20of%20the%20future%20for%20our%20society%2C%20it%20seems%20like%20a%20bad%20idea%20to%20destroy%20the%20sources%20of%20data%20that%20they%20were%20originally%20trained%20on.%20This%20is%20a%20concern%20shared%20by%20creative%20endeavours%20like%20the%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20authors%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Ftechnology-66866577%5C%22%3EGeorge%20R.R.%20Martin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20also%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F07%2F18%2Fmagazine%2Fwikipedia-ai-chatgpt.html%5C%22%3Eonline%20encyclopedia%20Wikipedia%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdvocates%20of%20large-scale%20data%20collection%20%E2%80%93%20like%20that%20used%20to%20power%20Large%20Language%20Models%20(LLMs)%2C%20the%20technology%20underlying%20AI%20chatbots%20such%20as%20ChatGPT%20%E2%80%93%20argue%20that%20AI%20systems%20%E2%80%9Ctransform%E2%80%9D%20the%20data%20they%20train%20on%20by%20%E2%80%9Clearning%E2%80%9D%20from%20their%20datasets%20and%20then%20creating%20something%20new.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22141125%2FSam-Altman-e1700642599137.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22141125%2FSam-Altman-e1700642599137.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22141125%2FSam-Altman-e1700642599137-300x150.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22141125%2FSam-Altman-e1700642599137-1024x512.jpeg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22141125%2FSam-Altman-e1700642599137-800x400.jpeg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685879%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESam%20Altman%20returns%20as%20OpenAI%20CEO.%20Photo%3A%20TechCrunch%2FFlickr%20CC%20BY%202.0%20DEED%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEffectively%2C%20what%20they%20mean%20is%20that%20researchers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Fresearch%2Ftechniques-for-training-large-neural-networks%5C%22%3Eprovide%20data%20written%20by%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20ask%20these%20systems%20to%20guess%20the%20next%20words%20in%20the%20sentence%2C%20as%20they%20would%20when%20dealing%20with%20a%20real%20question%20from%20a%20user.%20By%20hiding%20and%20then%20revealing%20these%20answers%2C%20researchers%20can%20provide%20a%20binary%20%E2%80%9Cyes%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cno%E2%80%9D%20answer%20that%20helps%20push%20AI%20systems%20towards%20accurate%20predictions.%20It%E2%80%99s%20for%20this%20reason%20that%20LLMs%20need%20vast%20reams%20of%20written%20texts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20were%20to%20copy%20the%20articles%20from%20the%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20website%20and%20charge%20people%20for%20access%2C%20most%20people%20would%20agree%20this%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Csystematic%20theft%20on%20a%20mass%20scale%E2%80%9D%20(as%20the%20newspaper%E2%80%99s%20lawsuit%20puts%20it).%20But%20improving%20the%20accuracy%20of%20an%20AI%20by%20using%20data%20to%20guide%20it%2C%20as%20shown%20above%2C%20is%20more%20complicated%20than%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirms%20like%20OpenAI%20do%20not%20store%20their%20training%20data%20and%20so%20argue%20that%20the%20articles%20from%20the%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20fed%20into%20the%20dataset%20are%20not%20actually%20being%20reused.%20A%20counter-argument%20to%20this%20defence%20of%20AI%2C%20though%2C%20is%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.zdnet.com%2Farticle%2Fchatgpt-can-leak-source-data-violate-privacy-says-googles-deepmind%2F%5C%22%3Ethere%20is%20evidence%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20systems%20such%20as%20ChatGPT%20can%20%E2%80%9Cleak%E2%80%9D%20verbatim%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnytco-assets.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F12%2FNYT_Complaint_Dec2023.pdf%5C%22%3Eexcerpts%20from%20their%20training%20data%3C%2Fa%3E.%20OpenAI%20says%20this%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Fblog%2Fopenai-and-journalism%5C%22%3Ea%20%E2%80%9Crare%20bug%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20suggests%20that%20these%20systems%20do%20store%20and%20memorise%20some%20of%20the%20data%20they%20are%20trained%20on%20%E2%80%93%20unintentionally%20%E2%80%93%20and%20can%20regurgitate%20it%20verbatim%20when%20prompted%20in%20specific%20ways.%20This%20would%20bypass%20any%20paywalls%20a%20for-profit%20publication%20may%20put%20in%20place%20to%20protect%20its%20intellectual%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELanguage%20use%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20is%20likely%20to%20have%20a%20longer%20term%20impact%20on%20the%20way%20we%20approach%20legislation%20in%20cases%20such%20as%20these%20is%20our%20use%20of%20language.%20Most%20AI%20researchers%20will%20tell%20you%20that%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Clearning%E2%80%9D%20is%20a%20very%20weighty%20and%20inaccurate%20word%20to%20use%20to%20describe%20what%20AI%20is%20actually%20doing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20must%20be%20asked%20whether%20the%20law%20in%20its%20current%20form%20is%20sufficient%20to%20protect%20and%20support%20people%20as%20society%20experiences%20a%20massive%20shift%20into%20the%20AI%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhether%20something%20builds%20on%20an%20existing%20copyrighted%20piece%20of%20work%20in%20a%20manner%20different%20from%20the%20original%20is%20referred%20to%20as%20%E2%80%9Ctransformative%20use%E2%80%9D%20and%20is%20a%20defence%20used%20by%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20these%20laws%20were%20designed%20to%20encourage%20people%20to%20remix%2C%20recombine%20and%20experiment%20with%20work%20already%20released%20into%20the%20outside%20world.%20The%20same%20laws%20were%20not%20really%20designed%20to%20protect%20multi-billion-dollar%20technology%20products%20that%20work%20at%20a%20speed%20and%20scale%20many%20orders%20of%20magnitude%20greater%20than%20any%20human%20writer%20could%20aspire%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problems%20with%20many%20of%20the%20defences%20of%20large-scale%20data%20collection%20and%20usage%20is%20that%20they%20rely%20on%20strange%20uses%20of%20the%20English%20language.%20We%20say%20that%20AI%20%E2%80%9Clearns%E2%80%9D%2C%20that%20it%20%E2%80%9Cunderstands%E2%80%9D%2C%20that%20it%20can%20%E2%80%9Cthink%E2%80%9D.%20However%2C%20these%20are%20analogies%2C%20not%20precise%20technical%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20like%20in%201954%2C%20when%20people%20looked%20at%20the%20modern%20equivalent%20of%20a%20broken%20calculator%20and%20called%20it%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbrain%E2%80%9D%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20using%20old%20language%20to%20grapple%20with%20completely%20new%20concepts.%20No%20matter%20what%20we%20call%20it%2C%20systems%20like%20ChatGPT%20do%20not%20work%20like%20our%20brains%2C%20and%20AI%20systems%20don%E2%80%99t%20play%20the%20same%20role%20in%20society%20that%20people%20play.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20we%20had%20to%20develop%20new%20words%20and%20a%20new%20common%20understanding%20of%20technology%20to%20make%20sense%20of%20computers%20in%20the%201950s%2C%20we%20may%20need%20to%20develop%20new%20language%20and%20new%20laws%20to%20help%20protect%20our%20society%20in%20the%202020s.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F220547%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fmike-cook-1501375%5C%22%3EMike%20Cook%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Senior%20Lecturer%2C%20Department%20of%20Informatics%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Fkings-college-london-1196%5C%22%3EKing%E2%80%99s%20College%20London%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fthe-new-york-times-lawsuit-against-openai-could-have-major-implications-for-the-development-of-machine-intelligence-220547%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705116610000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F12172655%2Fimage-1728.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fnyts-lawsuit-against-openai-could-have-major-implications-for-development-of-machine-intelligence%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20the%20crux%20of%20this%20issue%20is%20the%20question%20of%20data%20use.%20What%20data%20do%20companies%20like%20OpenAI%20have%20a%20right%20to%20use%2C%20and%20what%20do%20concepts%20like%20%E2%80%9Ctransform%E2%80%9D%20really%20mean%20in%20these%20con