%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Ftechnology-67959240.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Dog%20meat%3A%20Why%20is%20it%20a%20sensitive%20topic%20in%20South%20Korea%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705115399000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F12BAF%2Fproduction%2F_132291767_dog_meat_protest_getty.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-67958480%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20issue%20-%20which%20divides%20the%20nation%20along%20age%20lines%20-%20has%20come%20to%20the%20fore%20after%20a%20new%20law%20passed.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A397%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-67958480%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-67958480.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-67958480.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Notes%20from%20a%20Conference%3A%20A%20Critical%20Appraisal%20on%20Tamil%20Nadu%20as%20Land%20of%20Social%20Justice%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F12213716%2FEffect-66.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20makes%20%E2%80%98the%20other%E2%80%99%20(the%20dominant%20and%20upper%20caste)%20think%20that%20whatever%20they%20do%20against%20Dalits%2C%20they%20can%20justify%20in%20the%20court%20of%20law%2C%20in%20the%20society%20I%20live%20in%3F%20They%20cannot%20withstand%20what%20we%20wear%2C%20eat%2C%20and%2C%20if%20we%20speak%20good%20English%2C%20they%20feel%20threatened%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Professor%20N.%20Sukumar%20of%20the%20Delhi%20University%20while%20presenting%20at%20the%20event%20%E2%80%98Violence%20against%20Dalits%3A%20Interrogating%20the%20social%20justice%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%E2%80%99%20organised%20by%20Dalit%20Intellectual%20Collective%20(DIC)%20on%20January%206.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20one-day%20consultation%20brought%20together%20a%20diverse%20group%20of%20academic%20scholars%2C%20writers%2C%20legal%20practitioners%2C%20and%20activists%20to%20discuss%20and%20address%20the%20persistent%20issue%20of%20violence%20against%20Dalits%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20social%20justice%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDIC%20has%20released%20a%20public%20statement%20expressing%20its%20anguish%20and%20anxiety%20at%20the%20increasing%20instances%20of%20violence%20against%20Dalits%20%E2%80%93%20recently%20in%20Krishnagiri%2C%20Perambalur%2C%20Tirunelveli%2C%20and%20Nanguneri.%20The%20statement%20clearly%20mentions%20that%20the%20atrocities%20against%20Dalits%20should%20not%20be%20considered%20merely%20as%20a%20law%20and%20order%20problem%20but%20as%20caste%20Hindu%20hate%20politics%20as%20well%20%E2%80%93%20since%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20violence%20against%20Dalits%20have%20become%20normalised%2C%20forming%20a%20strong%20political%20culture%20in%20Tamilnadu%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20concept%20note%20of%20the%20event%20cites%20the%20data%20from%20the%20National%20Crime%20Records%20Bureau%20(NCRB)%2C%20in%20which%20crime%20against%20Dalits%20and%20tribals%20shows%20a%20persistent%20increase%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20compared%20to%20all-India%20data.%3Cbr%3E%5CnBetween%202019%20and%202021%2C%20the%20increase%20in%20crime%20against%20Dalits%20at%20the%20all-India%20level%20was%209.7%25%2C%20but%3Cbr%3E%5Cnit%20was%2016.92%25%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDIC%20questions%20the%20%E2%80%9Clukewarm%20response%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20government%20to%20these%20inhuman%20acts%2C%20which%20is%20alarming.%20Despite%20being%20propagated%20that%20the%20Dravidian%20land%20is%20a%20land%20of%20social%20justice%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%20has%20a%20long%20way%20to%20go%20to%20ensure%20social%20justice%20for%20Dalits%20on%20the%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fthere-is-an-urgent-need-to-address-how-caste-is-perceived-in-tamil-nadu%5C%22%3EThere%20Is%20an%20Urgent%20Need%20to%20Address%20How%20Caste%20Is%20Perceived%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolitical%20science%20Professor%20N.%20Sukumar%20expressed%20his%20anguish%2C%20mentioning%20the%20inhuman%20atrocity%20in%20Vengaivayal%2C%20where%20the%20human%20excreta%20was%20mixed%20in%20the%20drinking%20water%20tank%20of%20Dalit%20residents%20%E2%80%93%20the%20violation%20of%20a%20fundamental%20human%20right.%20He%20questions%20the%20silence%20of%20the%20ruling%20party%20on%20this%20issue%20in%20the%20land%20of%20Periyar.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20it%20%5BDravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%5D%20is%20committed%20to%20social%20justice%2C%20it%20should%20either%20do%20something%20to%20prevent%20such%20atrocities%20against%20Dalits%20or%20should%20not%20call%20it%20a%20social%20justice%20party.%E2%80%9D%20He%20further%20pointed%20out%20that%20it%20would%20result%20in%20trauma%20and%20agony%20for%20victims%20when%20they%20see%20perpetrators%20walk%20freely%2C%20which%20he%20said%2C%20clearly%20shows%20that%20judicial%20mechanisms%20are%20not%20being%20used%20to%20deliver%20justice%20to%20the%20victims%20but%20to%20the%20perpetrators.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDalit%20politics%20in%20the%20South%20is%20never%20complete%20without%20discussing%20the%20incidents%20of%20Karamchedu%20and%20Tsunduru%2C%20where%20Dalits%20were%20massacred%20by%20caste%20Hindus.%20Highlighting%20the%20same%2C%20Professor%20Srinivasulu%20Karli%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20of%20the%20Indian%20Council%20of%20Social%20Sciences%20Research%20(ICSSR)%2C%20spoke%20about%20the%20nuances%20of%20Dalit%20questions%20in%20Andhra%20and%20Telangana.%20Referring%20to%20those%20incidents%2C%20he%20stated%20that%20caste%20dynamics%20across%20the%20region%20are%20not%20uniform%20and%20contextually%20vary.%20While%20discussing%20the%20violence%20on%20Dalits%2C%20he%20said%20it%20is%20crucial%20to%20stress%20the%20violence%20mounted%20on%20Dalit%20women%20in%20all%20forms%20on%20an%20everyday%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShalin%20Maria%20Lawrence%2C%20a%20Dalit%20activist%20and%20writer%2C%20presented%20an%20intersectional%20approach%20to%20this%20issue%2C%20pointing%20out%20the%20violation%20of%20Dalit%20women%E2%80%99s%20bodies%20and%20minds%2C%20and%20the%20unending%20trauma%20of%20rapes%20affecting%20the%20Dalit%20psyche.%20She%20further%20highlighted%20the%20existing%20invisibility%20of%20caste%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Cpseudo-rationalism%20in%20the%20Dravidian%20state%20which%20has%20invisibilised%20caste%20and%20that%20invisibility%20gives%20caste%20the%20monstrous%20power%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20need%20for%20sensitisation%20on%20caste%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CInsensitivity%20compels%20a%20person%20to%20maintain%20the%20status%20quo%2C%20and%20any%20change%20in%20this%20is%20considered%20as%20a%20threat%20to%20this%20power.%20In%20some%20places%2C%20this%20insensitivity%20triggers%20violence%20or%20sympathises%20with%20perpetrators%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20P.%20Sivakami%2C%20a%20former%20IAS%20officer%20and%20Dalit%20feminist%20writer%2C%20emphasising%20the%20necessity%20to%20sensitise%20the%20rulers%20and%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20recalled%20her%20initiative%20%E2%80%98Sensitising%20the%20bureaucracy%20toward%20SC%2FST%20welfare%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20one-day%20experimental%20programme%20during%20the%20former%20chief%20minister%20Jayalalitha%E2%80%99s%20tenure.%20She%20revisited%20the%20challenges%20of%20conducting%20the%20programme%20for%20IAS%20and%20IPS%20officers.%20She%20elaborated%20on%20them%2C%20starting%20from%20the%20hurdles%20in%20getting%20approval%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20assistance%20from%20her%20colleagues%20to%20organise%2C%20where%20she%20had%20to%20do%20everything%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20first%20proposed%20this%20programme%20to%20the%20former%20chief%20minister%2C%20she%20questioned%20if%20it%20was%20possible%20to%20sensitise%20people%20who%20had%20not%20realised%20the%20plight%20of%20SC%2FST%20even%20after%2050%20years%20of%20independence.%20She%20replied%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20exercise%20is%20very%20limited%20because%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%C2%A0Prevention%20of%20Atrocities%20Act%20and%20Civil%20Rights%20Act%20is%20very%20poor%2C%20and%20hardly%207%25%20get%20convicted%2C%20and%2093%25%20escape%20from%20any%20punishment%20from%20these%20acts.%20So%2C%20our%20exercise%20is%20limited%20to%20that%20extent%2C%20how%20the%20government%20programmes%20could%20reach%20the%20Dalits.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20observing%20the%20general%20discussion%20on%20the%20reservation%20policy%2C%20%E2%80%9CDalits%20always%20feel%20that%20the%20government%20has%20done%20very%20little%20for%20them%20and%20the%20non-Dalits%20think%20all%20the%20programmes%20are%20targeted%20at%20SC%2FSTs.%20So%2C%20only%20through%20a%20dialogue%20between%20them%20can%20bridge%20the%20gap%20in%20understanding.%E2%80%9D%20When%20she%20said%20this%2C%20the%20former%20chief%20minister%20agreed%20to%20the%20programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F12214858%2Fevent-cover-picture.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22691%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F12214858%2Fevent-cover-picture.jpg%20691w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F12214858%2Fevent-cover-picture-300x207.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692760%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22477%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECover%20picture%20of%20the%20event.%20Photo%3A%20Special%20arrangement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECaste%20pride%20among%20youngsters%20and%20an%20imbalance%20in%20implementing%20reservation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Stalin%20Rajangam%2C%20a%20Tamil%20Scholar%20from%20south%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20presented%20his%20paper%20%E2%80%98Caste%20in%20the%20present%20times%3A%20Its%20breadth%20and%20depth%E2%80%99%2C%20expressing%20the%20shocking%20fact%20of%20increasing%20caste%20pride%20among%20students%2C%20especially%20from%20the%20ruling%2Fdominant%20castes.%20He%20spoke%20about%20direct%20and%20indirect%20symbolic%20indications%20of%20caste%20identity%20in%20different%20ways.%20Caste-coloured%20ropes%20are%20the%20predominant%20indicator%2C%20while%20others%20are%20in%20the%20form%20of%20banners%2C%20posters%2C%20t-shirts%2C%20stickers%2C%20and%20even%20songs%20representing%20particular%20caste%20identities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWitnessing%20caste%20practices%20among%20the%20students%20in%20south%20Tamil%20Nadu%20over%20the%20years%2C%20he%20strongly%20questioned%20why%20these%20practices%20did%20not%20change%20but%20are%20still%20retained%20in%20the%20land%20of%20social%20justice%20and%20how%20the%20state%20failed%20to%20prevent%20atrocities%20against%20Dalits.%20Further%2C%20the%20biggest%20problem%20is%20that%20it%20has%20been%20repeatedly%20narrated%20that%20these%20are%20Dalit%20issues%20for%20them%20to%20be%20concerned%20about.%20While%20questioning%20if%20the%20state%20has%20taken%20any%20kind%20of%20measures%20to%20engage%20with%20non-Dalits%20regarding%20caste%20issues%2C%20he%20underlined%20that%20these%20atrocities%20cannot%2Fwill%20not%20be%20changed%20without%20engaging%20with%20non-Dalits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20same%20panel%2C%20Professor%20Venkatanarayan%20from%20Christ%20University%2C%20Bangalore%2C%20discussed%20the%2069%25%20of%20reservation%20policy%20and%20violations%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20supported%20by%20the%20data%20gathered%20from%20the%20Sattanathan%20and%20Ambasankar%20Backward%20Class%20Commission%20reports.%20He%20stated%20that%20regardless%20of%20DMK%20coming%20up%20with%20an%20order%20on%20strict%20implementation%20of%20reservation%20in%201999%2C%20there%20is%20a%20continuing%20imbalance%20in%20implementation.%20Further%2C%20he%20urged%20the%20government%20to%20release%20a%20White%20Paper%20on%20beneficiaries%20of%20government%20jobs.%20He%20concluded%20by%20emphasising%20the%20importance%20of%20reservation%20policy%20which%20enables%20the%20marginalised%20communities%20to%20fight%20for%20social%20justice%20and%20against%20caste-based%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBrahmanical%20form%20of%20violence%20and%20cinema%20of%20violence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaving%20a%20series%20of%20discussions%20above%20on%20the%20physical%20and%20structural%20violence%20exhibited%20on%20Dalits%20by%20the%20dominant%20caste%20groups%20and%20the%20state%2C%20Professor%20P.%20Thirumal%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Hyderabad%20brought%20a%20stark%20criticism%20of%20Brahmanism%20and%20highlighted%20the%20Brahmanical%20violence%20which%20is%20indirect%2C%20invisiblised%20and%20more%20subtly%20normalised.%20Thirumal%2C%20for%20the%20last%20several%20years%2C%20has%20worked%20on%20caste%20violence%20in%20elite%20educational%20institutes%20in%20India%2C%20based%20on%20which%20he%20put%20forth%20that%20Brahmins%20create%20discomfort%20and%20indirectly%20discriminate%20Dalit-Bahujan%20students%2C%20which%20is%20more%20symbolic%20and%20cultural%2C%20not%20so%20visible%20but%20is%20naturalised.%20The%20physical%20violence%20made%20by%20the%20dominant%20castes%20can%20be%20seen%2C%20but%20this%20kind%20of%20Brahmanical%20violence%20under%20the%20mask%20of%20civility%20has%20been%20normalised%20over%20the%20long%20history%2C%20and%20he%20highlighted%20how%20the%20latter%20cannot%20be%20different%20from%20the%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20that%2C%20Dickens%20Leonard%2C%20assistant%20professor%20from%20IIT%20Delhi%2C%20added%20how%20Dalits%20in%20Tamil%20cinema%20are%20portrayed%20as%20nullified%20and%20static%20figures%20who%20are%20subjected%20to%20repeated%20violation%2C%20rejection%2C%20and%20humiliation.%20In%20his%20paper%20reflecting%20on%20the%20Tamil%20politics%20of%20caste%20as%20an%20aesthetic%20in%20cinema%2C%20he%20explored%20the%20relationship%20between%20violence%20and%20cinema%20as%20two%20conundrums%20or%20puzzles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdmk-karunanidhi-tamil-nadu-caste-politics%5C%22%3EThe%20DMK%20Has%20Been%20Two-Faced%20in%20Its%20Commitment%20Towards%20Social%20Justice%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELeonard%20also%20referred%20to%20an%20interesting%20concept%20proposed%20by%20S.%20Theodore%20Baskaran%2C%20one%20of%20the%20pioneers%20of%20cinema%20studies%20from%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20who%20states%20that%20Tamil%20cinema%20is%20a%20frontal%20cinema%20where%20an%20image%20or%20subject%20in%20front%20of%20you%20speaks%2C%20say%20the%20frontality%20in%20which%20the%20speech%20is%20offered%20in%20movies%20like%20Manohara%20and%20Parasakthi%2C%20replacing%20the%20God.%20Adding%20on%20to%20this%20discourse%20on%20frontality%2C%20highlighting%20aesthetic%20and%20political%20dimensions%20of%20Tamil%20cinema%2C%20he%20cited%20the%20character%20Rene%20from%20the%20movie%20Natchathiram%20Nagargiradhu%2C%20who%2C%20in%20one%20scene%20on%20a%20stage%2C%20says%20that%20she%20breaks%20like%20a%20mirror%2C%20yet%20she%20rebuilds%20herself%20as%20a%20theatre%20artist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENeglected%20manhole%20murders%20and%20eradication%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeepthi%20Sukumar%2C%20a%20Safai%20Karmachari%20Andolan%20core%20member%2C%20expressed%20her%20concerns%20about%20the%20lack%20of%20efforts%20or%20programmes%20to%20eradicate%20manual%20scavenging%20and%20prevent%20the%20deaths%20of%20workers%20in%20septic%20tanks.%20She%20highlighted%20that%20the%20state%20or%20Union%20governments%20have%20not%20recognised%20manual%20scavenging%20as%20a%20caste%20issue%20and%20have%20failed%20to%20take%20adequate%20measures%20to%20prevent%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F01%2F27162618%2FIMG_2018.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F01%2F27162618%2FIMG_2018.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F01%2F27162618%2FIMG_2018-300x169.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F01%2F27162618%2FIMG_2018-1024x576.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-578102%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeepthi%20further%20pointed%20out%20the%20flaws%20in%20the%20Swachh%20Bharat%20Abhiyan%20Mission%2C%20which%20aims%20to%20rehabilitate%3Cbr%3E%5Cnall%20manual%20scavengers%3B%20however%2C%20it%20builds%20more%20infrastructure%20ignoring%20the%20institutional%20caste%20violence%20which%20has%20been%20systematically%20done.%20She%20referred%20to%20the%20recent%20deaths%20of%20two%20manual%20scavengers%20in%20OCF%20(Ordnance%20Clothing%20Factory)%20staff%20quarters%20in%20Avadi%20and%20the%20immense%20pressure%20their%20families%20faced%20to%20withdraw%20the%20case.%20Despite%20the%20hopeless%20scenario%2C%20she%20expressed%20that%20the%20only%20thing%20we%20can%20do%20is%20keep%20fighting%20this%20kind%20of%20aggression%20we%20are%20living%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20event%20kicked%20off%20with%20the%20inaugural%20address%20by%20Justice%20B.%20G.%20Kolse%20Patil%2C%20retired%20judge%20of%20Bombay%20high%20court.%20He%2C%20alongside%20Professor%20Laxmanan%2C%20convenor%20of%20DIC%2C%20then%20released%20the%20books%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3ECaste%20Pride%3A%20Battle%20for%20Equality%20in%20Hindu%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20written%20by%20journalist%20Manoj%20Mitta%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3ECaste%20Discrimination%20and%20Exclusion%20in%20Indian%20Universities%3A%20A%20Critical%20Reflection%3C%2Fem%3E%20written%20by%20Professor%20N.%20Sukumar.%20Following%20this%2C%20the%20books%20were%20reviewed%20by%20advocate%20A.%20B.%20Rajasekaran%20and%20Prof.%20Lourdunathan%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20part%20of%20the%20consultation%20event%2C%20DIC%20presented%20the%20following%20demands%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1.%20The%20state%20government%20should%20release%20a%20White%20Paper%20on%20the%20Action%20Taken%20Report%20on%20atrocities%20against%20the%20Dalits%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2.%20The%20government%20should%20conduct%20regular%20periodic%20meetings%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20PoAct%20both%20at%20the%20district%20and%20state%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.%20Wherever%20or%20whenever%20violence%20against%20Dalits%20is%20committed%20the%20chief%20minister%2Fhome%20minister%20and%20chief%20secretary%20should%20visit%20the%20place%20and%20console%20the%20victims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E4.%20The%20government%20should%20constitute%20a%20high-level%20standing%20committee%20with%20representatives%20from%20all%20parties%20to%20discuss%20the%20violence%20against%20Dalits%20to%20recommend%20suitable%20remedies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E5.%20As%20in%20the%20past%2C%20the%20Rejuvenation%20of%20Self%20Respect%20movement%20%E2%80%93%20Removal%20of%20Caste%20Surname%20as%20prefixes%3Cbr%3E%5Cnand%20suffixes%20to%20individuals%20and%20institutions%20should%20be%20taken%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E6.%20Political%20parties%20should%20distance%20themselves%20from%20the%20criminals%20who%20are%20propagating%20caste%20pride%2Fhatred.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E7.%20The%20government%20should%20establish%20a%20centre%20in%20every%20school%2Fcollege%20and%20introduce%20Iyothee%20Thaas%2C%20Periyar%2C%20and%20Ambedkar%20thoughts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E8.%20The%20government%20should%20restart%20the%20sensitisation%20programme%20for%20bureaucracy%20at%20all%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E9.%20Every%20higher%20education%20institution%20should%20introduce%20sensitisation%20programme%20for%20the%20youth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E10.%20Every%20education%20institution%20should%20celebrate%20the%20Independence%20Day%20and%20the%20Constitution%3Cbr%3E%5CnDay%20in%20a%20grand%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E11.%20Like%20Kerala%2C%20a%20law%20should%20be%20enacted%20to%20provide%20reservation%20to%20children%20of%20inter-caste%20couples.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E12.%20The%20government%20(as%20promised)%20and%20civil%20society%20organisations%20should%20come%20forward%20for%20the%20total%20elimination%20of%20manual%20scavenging%20and%20manhole%20murders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E13.%20During%20calamities%2C%20sanitary%20workers%20should%20be%20paid%20an%20extra%20payment%20for%20their%20extra%20labour%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E14.%20Like%20the%20vigilance%20committee%2C%20an%20SC%2FST%20development%20committee%20should%20be%20constituted%20to%20monitor%20Sub%20Plan%20execution%20and%20provide%20a%20template%20for%20overall%20Dalit%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E15.%20The%20government%20should%20construct%20elevated%20houses%20for%20Chennai%20slum%20dwellers%20instead%20of%20uprooting%20them%20to%20Semmancheri%2C%20Kannagi%20Nagar%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E16.%20Re-introduce%20the%20scheme%20of%20providing%20two%20acres%20to%20landless%20agriculture%20workers%20in%20rural%20Tamil%20Nadu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E17.%2050%25%20of%20women%20should%20be%20given%20in%20the%20ministerial%20berths%20and%2050%25%20at%20every%20decision-making%3Cbr%3E%5Cnlevel%20of%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E18.%20The%20government%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%20and%20political%20parties%20should%20encourage%20the%20people%20towards%20Buddhism%20and%20should%20have%20regular%20programme%20for%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ELalitha%20is%20a%20PhD%20scholar%20in%20Urban%20Studies%20from%20IIT%20Madras%2C%20and%20holds%20a%20Master%E2%80%99s%20degree%20in%20Sociology%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Hyderabad.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705114857000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F12213716%2FEffect-66.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fnotes-from-a-conference-a-critical-appraisal-on-tamil-nadu-as-land-of-social-justice%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Speakers%20at%20the%20'Violence%20against%20Dalits%3A%20Interrogating%20social%20justice%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu'%20conference%20organised%20by%20Dalit%20Intellectual%20Collective%20spoke%20extensively%20about%20the%20steps%20required%20to%20tackle%20rising%20caste%20atrocities%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fnotes-from-a-conference-a-critical-appraisal-on-tamil-nadu-as-land-of-social-justice%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rashid%20Khan%3A%20The%20maestro%20who%20took%20classical%20music%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20masses%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705113877000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F5A08%2Fproduction%2F_132284032_rk_1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-67942757%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20short%20career%2C%20Rashid%20Khan%20-%20who%20died%20earlier%20this%20week%20-%20became%20the%20foremost%20exponents%20of%20classical%20music.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A121%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-67942757%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-67942757.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-67942757.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20Refuse%20to%20Give%20Readers%20Everything%20on%20a%20Platter%3A%20Vivek%20Shanbhag%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F12180213%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-01-12-at-6.01.38-PM.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKozhikode%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%E2%80%9CGlobalisation%20and%20an%20open%20market%20have%20had%20an%20immense%20impact%20on%20everyday%20lives%2C%E2%80%9D%20author%20Vivek%20Shanbhag%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20has%20come%20with%20a%20loss%20of%20ideology%2C%20which%20has%20not%20been%20replaced%20with%20anything%20else.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShanbhag%2C%20speaking%20at%20a%20session%20at%20the%20Kerala%20Literature%20Festival%20on%20Friday%20(January%2012)%20on%20his%20book%3Cem%3E%20Sakina%E2%80%99s%20Kiss%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20was%20explaining%20why%20his%20protagonist%20Venkat%20%E2%80%93%20like%20many%20others%20in%20society%20%E2%80%93%20is%20confused%2C%20and%20why%20this%20confusion%20has%20led%20to%20the%20growth%20of%20the%20right%20wing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESakina%E2%80%99s%20Kiss%3C%2Fem%3E%20follows%20a%20family%20%E2%80%93%20Venkat%2C%20his%20wife%20Viji%20and%20their%20daughter%20Rekha%20%E2%80%93%20through%20four%20days%20of%20their%20lives%2C%20as%20they%20navigate%20certain%20extraordinary%20circumstances%20and%20a%20chasm%20in%20their%20relationships%20(particularly%20Venkat%E2%80%99s%20relationships%20with%20Viji%20and%20Rekha).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShanbhag%20is%20the%20author%20of%20nine%20books%20and%20three%20plays%20in%20Kannada%2C%20and%20has%20co-translated%20U.R.%20Ananthamurthy%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EHindutva%20or%20Hind%20Swaraj%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20English.%20%3Cem%3ESakina%E2%80%99s%20Kiss%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20Shanbhag%E2%80%99s%20second%20novel%20to%20be%20translated%20to%20English%2C%20after%20%3Cem%3EGhachar%20Ghochar%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Both%20have%20been%20translated%20from%20Kannada%20by%20Srinath%20Perur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20festival%2C%20Shanbhag%20spoke%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20about%20his%20books%2C%20their%20context%20and%20more.%20Edited%20excerpts%20from%20the%20conversation%20follow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20spoke%20in%20the%20session%20today%20about%20the%20impact%20of%20globalisation%20and%20the%20changes%20that%20has%20brought%2C%20and%20the%20influence%20that%20has%20had%20on%20your%20work.%20But%20the%20way%20you%20look%20at%20some%20of%20those%20changes%20is%20rooted%20in%20the%20family%2C%20and%20the%20internal%20dynamics%20of%20families.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20kind%20of%20changes%20that%20we%20see%20%E2%80%93%20it%20is%20not%20possible%20to%20escape%20globalisation.%20And%20that%20has%20brought%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20changes.%20We%20are%20not%20in%20a%20position%20to%20say%20whether%20that%20is%20good%20or%20bad%2C%20because%20it%20is%20a%20mixed%20bag.%20It%20is%20difficult%20to%20take%20a%20stand%20on%20it.%20How%20do%20we%20feel%20any%20change%3F%20We%20feel%20the%20change%20when%20it%20impacts%20a%20person.%20In%20India%2C%20the%20family%20is%20the%20smallest%20unit%2C%20unlike%20the%20West%20where%20the%20individual%20is%20the%20smallest%20unit.%20So%20anything%20that%20impacts%20the%20family%20impacts%20us%20as%20individuals.%20And%20I%20see%20the%20changes%20brought%20in%20by%20globalisation%2C%20the%20conflict%20it%20has%20resulted%20in%2C%20has%20impacted%20families.%20And%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20I%20was%20talking%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20both%20the%20books%20that%20have%20been%20translated%20into%20English%2C%20there%20are%20male%20protagonists%20who%20have%20had%20their%20masculinities%20questioned%2C%20internally%20within%20the%20family%2C%20and%20then%20they%20act%20in%20reaction%20to%20that.%20Is%20that%20because%20of%20how%20much%20you%20see%20this%20happening%20around%20us%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20changes%20have%20happened%20in%20a%20system%20where%20women%20did%20not%20have%20access%20to%20knowledge%2C%20where%20they%20weren%E2%80%99t%20exposed%2C%20or%20where%20they%20were%20curtailed%20or%20controlled%20or%20oppressed%20in%20some%20way.%20With%20globalisation%2C%20the%20money%20that%20has%20flowed%20in%20has%20enabled%20awareness.%20The%20kind%20of%20exposure%20that%20women%20have%2C%20girl%20children%20have%2C%20has%20changed%20in%20our%20society.%20And%20I%20think%20that%20has%20brought%20out%20a%20big%20change.%20And%20that%20is%20being%20challenged%20%E2%80%93%20if%20you%20see%20in%20smaller%20places%2C%20in%20smaller%20families%2C%20everywhere%20it%20is%20being%20challenged.%20And%20there%20lies%20the%20big%20change%3B%20not%20just%20the%20challenge%2C%20but%20the%20moment%20you%20challenge%2C%20there%20is%20a%20conflict.%20I%20see%20that%20everywhere.%20And%20the%20rise%20of%20all%20that%20we%20see%20of%20the%20right%20wing%20%E2%80%93%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20my%20novel%20is%20trying%20to%20say%20%E2%80%93%20is%20a%20response%20to%20this%20challenge.%20Because%20people%20want%20to%20retain%20control%2C%20they%20want%20to%20control%20women%3A%20how%20they%20dress%2C%20what%20they%20say%2C%20everything.%20Which%20is%20why%20I%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20there%20in%20these%20two%20novels.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20like%20I%20write%20only%20about%20this%2C%20but%20it%20so%20happened%20that%20these%20issues%20have%20seeped%20in%2C%20because%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20you%20see%20around%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EParticularly%20from%20%3Cem%3ESakina%E2%80%99s%20Kiss%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20it%20suggests%20you%20believe%20stories%2C%20like%20life%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20need%20to%20have%20a%20conventional%20ending%2C%20where%20things%20are%20neatly%20wrapped%20up.%20Is%20that%20a%20fair%20assumption%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3ESee%2C%20it%20is%20also%20a%20literary%20tool%20where%20you%20have%20an%20open%20end.%20An%20open%20ending%20is%20not%20done%20because%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20how%20to%20end%20the%20story%2C%20there%20is%20a%20specific%20reason%20for%20it.%20And%20the%20reason%20is%20that%20when%20there%20are%20options%20opened%20up%2C%20and%20you%20have%20to%20choose%20one%20of%20the%20options%2C%20as%20a%20reader%20that%E2%80%99s%20a%20responsibility%20that%20you%20take.%20That%20is%20a%20point%20I%20am%20trying%20to%20make.%20That%20any%20option%20that%20you%20choose%2C%20any%20ending%20that%20you%20pick%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20responsibility%20on%20you%2C%20not%20on%20the%20writer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20reason%20I%20have%20done%20that%20is%20also%20that%20today%20we%20are%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20%E2%80%93%20be%20it%20in%20TV%20debates%2C%20media%2C%20anywhere%20%E2%80%93%20people%20wanted%20everything%20to%20be%20discussed%20and%20for%20them%20to%20be%20given%20an%20opinion.%20Everything%20has%20to%20be%20given%20on%20a%20platter%2C%20people%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20think.%20Which%20is%20one%20of%20the%20problems%20today%2C%20and%20also%20it%20has%20brought%20this%20agitation%2C%20this%20discouragement%2C%20around%20questioning%20that%20we%20see.%20And%20this%20repression%20in%20the%20current%20regime%2C%20wherever%20you%20see.%20Thinking%20is%20not%20encouraged.%20And%20people%20want%20the%20writer%20to%20resolve%20everything%20and%20give%20it%20on%20a%20platter.%20I%20refuse%20to%20do%20it%20%E2%80%93%20though%20all%20my%20novels%20are%20not%20like%20this%20%E2%80%93%20because%20in%20certain%20cases%2C%20I%20would%20really%20like%20the%20reader%20to%20get%20involved%20and%20take%20responsibility%20for%20the%20ending.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20wanted%20to%20ask%20you%20about%20translations%2C%20since%20you%E2%80%99ve%20been%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20exercise.%20How%20do%20you%20make%20those%20choices%20%E2%80%93%20that%20these%20are%20the%20two%20books%20of%20yours%20that%20would%20be%20translated%20first%20to%20English%2C%20and%20also%20about%20which%20book%20you%20decided%20to%20translate%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%20that%20I%20have%20chosen%20to%20translate%20is%20also%20a%20kind%20of%20a%20political%20statement.%20I%20felt%20that%20the%20book%20was%20really%20the%20need%20of%20the%20hour.%20The%20reason%20I%20got%20involved%20in%20it%20is%20also%20because%20of%20Ananthamurthy%2C%20this%20was%20his%20last%20book%20and%20more%20information%20was%20required%20to%20bring%20clarity%20to%20the%20text.%20And%20I%20thought%20I%20had%20that%20access%20%5BAnanthamurthy%20was%20Shanbhag%E2%80%99s%20father-in-law%5D%20and%20that%20how%20I%20got%20involved.%20It%E2%80%99s%20also%20a%20beautiful%20text%2C%20a%20very%20strong%20expression%20of%20the%20concerns%20of%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20Srinath%20%5BPerur%5D%2C%20I%20knew%20Srinath%20for%20a%20long%20time%20and%20he%E2%80%99s%20a%20creative%20writer%2C%20though%20he%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20published%20anything.%20I%20like%20his%20language%2C%20I%20liked%20his%20sensibility%2C%20I%20liked%20his%20book%20(the%20travelogue%20%3Cem%3EIf%20It%E2%80%99s%20Monday%20This%20Must%20Be%20Madurai%3C%2Fem%3E).%20So%20I%20went%20to%20him%20and%20asked%20him%20if%20he%20would%20want%20to%20do%20a%20translation.%20He%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20done%20any%20translations%20till%20then.%20This%20%5B%3Cem%3EGhachar%20Ghochar%3C%2Fem%3E%5D%20is%20his%20first%20translation%20ever.%20And%20that%20is%20how%20this%20relationship%20began.%20There%20is%20always%20a%20lot%20of%20discussion%2C%20there%20are%20many%20things%20that%20go%20into%20coming%20out%20with%20these%20translations.%20And%20I%20have%20thoroughly%20enjoyed%20working%20on%20both%20these%20translations%20with%20him.%20He%E2%80%99s%20a%20very%20insightful%20literary%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20recently%20had%20a%20short%20story%20out%20in%20%3Cem%3EMint%20Lounge%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20in%20which%20the%20protagonist%20is%20a%20writer.%20One%20of%20his%20beliefs%20is%20that%20this%20idea%20that%20writing%20happens%20better%20in%20solitude%20is%20not%20necessarily%20true.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%E2%80%99s%20making%20fun%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYes%2C%20exactly.%20Is%20that%20a%20reflection%20of%20your%20beliefs%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20story.%20I%20have%20written%20in%20all%20kinds%20of%20circumstances%2C%20because%20I%20was%20working.%20Many%20times%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20that%20choice.%20But%20it%20is%20important%20to%20disconnect%20your%20mind%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20at%20the%20time%20of%20writing%2C%20so%20that%20it%20is%20filled%20with%20your%20own%20story%2C%20your%20own%20characters%2C%20and%20it%20is%20not%20distracting.%20Because%20one%20needs%20a%20certain%20kind%20of%20heightened%20sensibility%2C%20heightened%20imagination%20to%20write.%20So%20to%20that%20extent%20that%20cut%20off%20is%20necessary%2C%20but%20it%20might%20not%20need%20to%20be%20a%20physical%20cut%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705113052000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F12180213%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-01-12-at-6.01.38-PM.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fi-refuse-to-give-readers-everything-on-a-platter-vivek-shanbhag%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22On%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20Kerala%20Literature%20Festival%2C%20Shanbhag%20spoke%20to%20The%20Wire%20about%20his%20books%2C%20their%20context%20and%20more.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fi-refuse-to-give-readers-everything-on-a-platter-vivek-shanbhag%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20launches%20new%20strike%20against%20Houthi%20target%20in%20Yemen%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705108800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F01%2F768x432%2Fskynews-yemen-sanaa-houthi_64200